						<div class="postbody">When it goes into the &quot;infinite loop&quot; part, are the index registers in 16-bit mode?  Also, I think &quot;ldy #$00&quot; might have issues with assemblers if it is used in 16-bit mode, since it is written as an 8-bit number.  Better write it as &quot;ldy #$0000&quot; to make sure it assembles correctly.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">InfiniteLoop:<br />wai<br /><br />php&nbsp; ;;I don't know what mode it was in, but this saves it on stack<br /><br />rep #$20<br />ldy #$0000<br />ldx #MetaspriteTable<br />sty YTemp<br />stx XTemp<br />jsr start_metasprite<br /><br />plp&nbsp; ;;This returns to whatever mode it was, assuming that it is in the correct mode for the rest of the code<br /></div></div>

